Geometrically, $|z + 5 - 3i|$ is the distance between the complex numbers $z$ and $-5 + 3i$ in the complex plane, and $|z - 7 + 2i|$ is the distance between $z$ and $7 - 2i.$

[asy]
unitsize(0.4 cm);

pair A, B, Z;

A = (-5,3);
B = (7,-2);
Z = (6,6);

draw(A--B);
draw(A--Z--B);

dot("$-5 + 3i$", A, NW);
dot("$7 - 2i$", B, SE);
dot("$z$", Z, NE);
[/asy]

By the Triangle Inequality, the sum of the distances is minimized when $z$ lies on the line segment connecting the two complex numbers $-5 + 3i$ and $7- 2i,$ in which case the sum of the distances is simply $|(5 - 3i) - (-7 + 2i)| = |12 - 5i| = \boxed{13}.$

