Let
\[f(x) = \left\{
\begin{array}{cl}
2x & \text{if $0 \le x < 2$}, \\
8 - 2x & \text{if $2 \le x \le 4$}.
\end{array}
\right.\]Find the maximum value of the function. ||| For $0 \le x < 2,$\n\[f(x) = 2x = 4, \text{ at } x = 2.\]\\ For $2 \le x \le 4,$\n\[f(x) = 8 - 2x = 0, \text{ at } x = 4.\]\\ Therefore, the maximum value of $f(x)$ is $\boxed{4}$.

